Senator Shehu Sani, representing Kaduna Central at the National Assembly, has condemned the killings of British tourist at Kajuru castle in Kajuru Local Government Area of Kaduna State. The Senator said the killing of the female expatriate “stands condemned in stronger term”. In a short condolence message twitted on his twitter handle, Senator Sani extended his condolences to the family of the victims of the attack. “The Killing of Faye Mooney and one other by Kidnappers and the abduction of others from Kajuru castle, Kaduna state stands condemned. “My ‎condolences to the families of the victims and the Government of the UK,” he said. Late Miss Mooney was killed by Kidnappers on ‎Friday at the top hill. She was there with her colleagues from Lagos. The State Police Command identified the female expatriate as British citizen and a staff of Mercy Corps Nigeria. JUST IN: Police confirm Briton killed in Kajuru attack Kajuru abduction: British female tourist killed in Kaduna – Police Shehu Sani condemns killing of 12 soldiers in Kaduna village